author: Journal Inquirer Staff
title: King’s goal helps EC halt winless streak
text:
King’s goal helps EC halt winless streak By Journal Inquirer Staff Journal Inquirer | 0 comments 
In one fell swoop, the East Catholic High boys soccer team snapped a four-game winless streak, and avenged a loss from earlier this season. 
Kyle King’s goal snapped a 1-1 tie with 20 minutes remaining as East Catholic held on for a 2-1 Central Connecticut Conference North victory at Hartford Public on Wednesday.
